      "question": "Find the roots of the quadratic equation $x^2 + 5x - 24 = 0$ by the method of factorisation.",
      "answer": "$x = 3, -8$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Find two numbers whose product is $-24$ and sum is $5$. These numbers are $8$ and $-3$.",
          "Split the middle term $5x$ as $8x - 3x$ and factorise the expression to find the roots."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^2 + 5x - 24 = 0 \\\\ x^2 + 8x - 3x - 24 = 0 \\\\ x(x + 8) - 3(x + 8) = 0 \\\\ (x - 3)(x + 8) = 0 \\\\ x - 3 = 0 \\text{ or } x + 8 = 0 \\\\ x = 3, x = -8$"
      },
